text: Liiva-Putla Nature Reserve is a nature reserve situated on Saaremaa island in western Estonia, in Saare County. Liiva-Putla Nature Reserve is one of only five nature reserves in Europe created for the protection of fungi. Estonian mycologist Erast Parmasto was one of the main people behinds its creation. Today it forms part of the EU-wide Natura 2000-network and contains twelve rare species of fungi. ==References== Category:Nature reserves in Estonia Category:Geography of Saare County Category:Saaremaa Parish
